-1 HIGHPRIEST~

     The position of High Priest of a God/Goddess is one of great honor.
To be a High Priest means that you have proven your self to be worthy in
the ways of Bravery, Wisdom, Brotherhood, and Love for your God/Goddess.
With the honor of being High Priest, you also recieve the sceptor of the
God/Goddess, and a room withing the clan city walls.  You'll also be able
to use the clan channel to talk to everyone thats on!  Although, with
these rewards come great responsibility.  If anything goes wrong within
your clan, or something happens to your clan...you are responsible for
it.  You also oversee the actions of the members, and their devotion to
the patron God/Goddess.  If you think that you are worthy of this awesome
responsibility and honor, pray to your clan God/Goddess for more 
information.
~

-1 AFFECTS AFFECT~
This command is used to show all the spells affecting your character. At
low levels, only the spell name will be displayed, at higher levels the
effects and duration of the spell will also be shown.  Spell effects
are no longer shown on score (this can be changed by using 'show' command).
~

0 DRAVEN~
                 >---Lord Draven Daviau of Maduro---<
____________________________________________________________________________

     Born to a street cleaner in the dark city of Maduro, Draven Daviau 
 suffered ridicule and harrasment.  Draven was a Creole boy in a Spanish
 city, and the two did not bode well with one another.  One night, his
 mother asked him, "What troubles you young one?"  Draven responded, "I
 feel like a dirty animal, howling inside, being kicked like a dog, and
 I'm losing control."  Choking back a bit of laughter his mother said, "I 
 don't understand..."  Those were the last words she ever spoke.  Out of
 utter insanity, Draven killed both of his parents, and then fled into the 
 wooded swamplands.  
      There he lived on insects and swamp water.  Gators soon became no 
 match for Draven, as he quickly learned to outsmart them.  One night,
 sitting in a make-shift canoe of gator skin and willow branches, Draven
 was attacked by "something."  It left him in a pit, weak and on death's
 door.  In a room without a light, or view, unable to move his limbs, 
 Draven waited to die.  Thrice nights thereafter, a dark being visited
 Draven.  "What if I can give you a new life, better than the one you
 had?"
 "I'd think you were a god." Draven mumbled.  The creature took him, and
 drained the life from him.  Then it made Draven drink the blood from it's
 core.  Cut and broken, Draven was all but dead, and then the pain started.
 His skin stretched so tightly he screamed for the mercy of the gods.  A
 burning sensation spread from his core to his limbs...and the he felt ALIVE!
 Draven had been borne to the children of darkness.  There he stayed with
 them and learned their dark ways.  
      Some years later, on a night with a new moon, the tribe was attacked
 by humans and set fire to.  Draven and a few others escaped, and fled into
 seperate directions.  He finally came to rest in a french town cemetery.
 The next night, he decided to visit the church.  There he met up with a 
 young priest.  This was a very philosophical priest, who would sit and
 discuss the issues of goodness with Draven.  There Draven learned the life
 of the "good man," and even lived it for awhile.  One night Draven stumbled
 upon some old writings scattered about in the priest's study.  He translated
 them quickly and found they described a god who was the "god of gods," Ao.
 Draven soon began worshiping Ao like none other before him.  He even took a
 vow of silence for a while in respect of Ao.  Trouble had started up in a 
 far land, with an evil god by the name of Beowolf behind it.  One night, 
 Draven was visited by Ao, and asked to become a true immortal.  Draven
 jumped at the chance, and soon studied with Ao for many years.  A god by
 the name of Allanon approached Draven one day to see if he would team up
 with Allanon in the Immortal war that was going on.  Draven agreed, and 
 joined Allanon in the war.  
     When the war was disbanded by Ao, Draven requested to be appointed as
a god of neutrality.  Considering the facts that Draven had knowledge of
both the good and dark sides; plus the fact that he has studied with Ao for
many years, he was granted the godship.  Draven returned to his birth place 
of Maduro.  He slayed all those that chose not to follow him in revenge of
his childhood, and then burried the city.  Draven bacame a minstrel, singing
the songs of his adventures.  Many people saw Draven's knowledge of the 
forces, and his respect for the free will of others.  They chose to worship
Draven, and joined his religion of Maduro.

